P* 1833 a A.GAB I II E T.LEAGUE OP NATIONS.PROPOSED AGENDA FOR THE 9TH SESSION OP THECOUNCIL TO BE HELD ON SSPTEIvlBER 16TH. 1920.Additional SubjectDISPUTE BETOEN POLAND AND LITHUANIA.Tele am to the Members of the Council.(Circulated for information with reference to CP. 1833.)Following the communication from the Polish Government, which was telegraphed to the Members Of the Council on September 7th, and after consultation with the acting President of the Council, the dispute between Poland and Lithuania will be placed on the Agenda of the meeting of the Council, on September 16th in Faris* Further documents relating ,ta this question will be forwarded as soon as possible.ANZILOTTI.Acting Secretary-Generaleierland House, Curzon Street, London, W.l.8th September, 1920.
